---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Return the shield content.
@lot: $in, $fail = false, $print = true
@static: 1
@example: |
  Route::set('foo/bar', function() {
      return Shield::get('foo/bar', [
          'title' => 'Test Title',
          'description' => 'Test description.'
      ]);
  });
@result: |
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
    <head>
      <meta charset="utf-8">
      <title><?php echo $lot['title']; ?></title>
    </head>
    <body>
      <h1><?php echo $lot['title']; ?></h1>
      <p><?php echo $lot['description']; ?></p>
    </body>
  </html>
@result-description: Content of `foo.php`, `foo\bar.php` or any path defined by [`Shield::set()`][link:set] for the `foo/bar`:
